(remains the authoritative identifier internally.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How addresses are derived internally \(HPK\)) Tj
T*
(- Public key ? SHA3-384 ? HPK \(hashed public key\) ? Base56 address.) Tj
T*
(- The Base56 address is a user-friendly wrapper; internally the node works with the HPK bytes) Tj
T*
(for lookups \(UTXO, mempool, wallet\).) Tj
T*
(- Network prefix: Mainnet addresses use A as the leading letter; Testnet uses T to avoid) Tj
T*
(cross-network confusion.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Examples \(address ? HPK\)) Tj
T*
(- Mainnet address \(prefix A\):) Tj
T*
(  A9PDGuRfXS2s6Mpq5NSrug4x5vHxRcfQer3PbWUxjyRTQ7h8NcTHMyvpXy4CxM6FMnySAwpYgs) Tj
T*
(  Corresponding HPK \(SHA3-384, human-readable tag\):) Tj
T*
(  ATHO685591341486bd81bbf6b705dff4e2375d17e06b04ae1f0c241b968107f17406fdedeacfa9301bc6e927118d7a) Tj
T*
(e86577) Tj
T*
(- Testnet address \(prefix T\):) Tj
T*
(  T84Eh9SrqHhXSffCGgTj7kRYuqJcdh2XmxPpY3Z97n42jwEU2FDNZWD8ExkYCFtaJZ8t72SaPe) Tj
T*
(  Corresponding HPK \(SHA3-384, human-readable tag\):) Tj
T*
(  ATHT5579ff037417a01d019e4edfaa7d3fb9b784bb0f4f5de63e89da1e403a727b2767df338a849869c8a2f27671ad) Tj
T*
(5c857b) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These examples illustrate the friendly, reduced alphabet \(no lookalikes\), clear network prefix,) Tj
T*
(and the internal HPK \(SHA3-384\) that the node uses for validation and storage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why SHA3-384 \(vs. other SHA3 variants\)) Tj
T*
(- We chose SHA3-384 for extra collision resistance margin over SHA3-256 while keeping addresses) Tj
T*
(manageable; it?s a conservative ?overkill? choice aligned with using Falcon-512.) Tj
T*
(- Shorter digests reduce address length but also reduce collision/preimage headroom:) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-128 \(~28 chars in Base56\) ? not secure enough.) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-224 \(~44 chars\) ? tighter, but less margin.) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-256 \(~49 chars\) ? a good balance, but we opted for more headroom.) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-384 \(~71 chars\) ? our canonical choice \(current Atho addresses\).) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-512 \(~93 chars\) ? stronger but longer; not needed given Falcon-512 and our threat model.) Tj
T*
(- Encoding does not weaken the hash; Base56 just makes the bytes human-friendly. Internally, the) Tj
T*
(full digest is used for HPK comparisons and UTXO/mempool lookups.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Sample Base56 addresses by SHA3 variant \(for illustration\)) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-128 \(~28 chars, not secure enough\):) Tj
T*
(  APx9RkGm7TsY4WbZpQ2hNfJcD5Mv) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-224 \(~44 chars\):) Tj
T*
(  AfxT7Pw9qGmVhzp8sETwYQkCm3NsdvJxrE2PzQ4sQJtW) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-256 \(~49 chars, balanced\):) Tj
T*
(  AdwP5KxrVfTs8FGYkchLHt9RrS8zWpY7q9bZ2dkmwQ8J2VNxx) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-384 \(~71 chars, chosen\):) Tj
T*
(  Akv4QGm29xWYPjvTFeqbrncHtWs2KyMa9R7fz8bHdpPx6LGrgxJt3WcPGykGsDRfpN8J) Tj
T*
(- SHA3-512 \(~93 chars, longer than needed\):) Tj
T*
(  AhQwT7Lm9dKs3GyPVb4ZRnqSH8MtWcF2xE5JrUu9TwGmCqP7vXaLzRM8YtHfS6JpGkV3SdBtQwNnLkHcF9XsDpM) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Where it?s used) Tj
T*
(- CLI address display, wallet exports, and transaction inputs.) Tj
T*
(- Node APIs that return or accept addresses.) Tj
T*
(- Internally, addresses map back to HPK for lookup in UTXO and mempool.) Tj
T*
